Let \( \mu^{G}_{X,Y}: G(X)\otimes_2 G(Y)\xrightarrow{\;\cong\;}G(X\otimes_2 Y) \) be the monoidal structure of the strong monoidal functor \(G\).
For every morphism \(f:X\to X'\) and object \(Y\) we have
\[
G(f\otimes_2\mathrm{id}_Y)=
\mu^{G}_{X',Y}{}^{-1}\;\circ\;
\bigl(G(f)\otimes_2\mathrm{id}_{G(Y)}\bigr)\;\circ\;
\mu^{G}_{X,Y}.
\]
Taking \(X=F(U\otimes_1 V),\;X'=F(U)\otimes_2 F(V),\;f=F(U,V),\;Y=F(W)\) gives
\[
G\!\bigl(F(U,V)\otimes_2\mathrm{id}_{F(W)}\bigr)=
\mu^{G}_{F(U)\otimes_2 F(V),\,F(W)}^{-1}\;
\circ\;
\bigl(G(F(U,V))\otimes_2\mathrm{id}_{G(F(W))}\bigr)\;
\circ\;
\mu^{G}_{F(U\otimes_1 V),\,F(W)},
\]
so the two morphisms are only canonically isomorphic, not equal in general.
